goals.question: What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?
goals.visualization: line chart of unemployment rate over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if the unemployment rate has been increasing or decreasing over the years.

goals.question: Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in 2010?
goals.visualization: bar chart of unemployment rate by industry in 2010
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the industry that had the highest unemployment rate in the most recent year of the dataset.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the number of unemployed individuals across all industries?
goals.visualization: histogram of count of unemployed individuals
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of the number of unemployed individuals across all industries.

goals.question: Which industry had the highest number of unemployed individuals in 2005?
goals.visualization: bar chart of count of unemployed individuals by industry in 2005
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the industry that had the highest number of unemployed individuals in a specific year.

goals.question: What is the correlation between the number of unemployed individuals and the unemployment rate?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of count of unemployed individuals vs unemployment rate
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the relationship between the number of unemployed individuals and the unemployment rate in each industry.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='rate', hue='series', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Industry', loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data_2010 = data[data['year'] == 2010]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='series', y='rate', data=data_2010, ci=None)
    plt.title('Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Industry')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Industry', loc='upper right', labels=data_2010['series'].unique())

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', bins=30, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['count'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the number of unemployed individuals across all industries?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Number of Unemployed Individuals")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data_2005 = data[data['year'] == 2005]
    industry_counts = data_2005.groupby('series')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    max_count = industry_counts['count'].max()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='series', y='count', data=industry_counts)
    ax.axhline(max_count, ls='--', color='red', label=f'Max count: {max_count:.2f}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Industry')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Unemployed Individuals')
    plt.title('Which industry had the highest number of unemployed individuals in 2005?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
